
@*
Procurement Tracking Tool
    CSIS 483 Capstone Project
    Moses Padilla

    Purpose:
    This page serves as the main landing page for the Procurement Tracking Tool. It provides users with a central navigation interface to access the core
    procurement management functions within the application.

    Functionality:
    - Displays the application welcome screen.
    - Introduces the purpose of the Procurement Tracking Tool.
    - Provides navigation to the Create Purchase Request page.
    - Provides navigation to the View/Approve Purchase Requests page.
    - Provides navigation to the Vendor List page.
    - Serves as the primary entry point into the procurement workflow tracker.

    Notes:
    This page was developed using ASP.NET Core Razor Views and Bootstrap components. Navigation buttons utilize ASP.NET MVC controller and action
    routing to direct users to the appropriate application functions. The page supports usability and accessibility by providing a simple, centralized interface 
    for procurement activities.

    References:
    Carey, P. M. (2020). New perspectives on HTML5 and CSS3: Comprehensive (8th ed.). Cengage Learning.

    Microsoft. (n.d.). Razor syntax reference for ASP.NET Core. https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/mvc/views/razor
*@


@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Procurement Tracking Tool";
}

<div class="text-center">
    <h1>Welcome to the Procurement Tracking Tool</h1>

    <p>This system helps track procurement requests from creation to approval.</p>

    <div class="mt-4">
        <a class="btn btn-primary m-2" asp-controller="PurchaseRequest" asp-action="Create">
            Create Purchase Request
        </a>

        <a class="btn btn-success m-2" asp-controller="PurchaseRequest" asp-action="Approve">
            View/Approve Purchase Requests
        </a>

        <a class="btn btn-secondary m-2" asp-controller="PurchaseRequest" asp-action="Vendors">
            Vendor List
        </a>
    </div>
</div>